      <blockquote> 
        <h2 align="left">Add Integer</font></h2>
        <p align="left">Next Mike H. adds an integer value to the simulation.</p>
      </blockquote>
      <ul>
        <li>Integers values can be uses for a variety of different purposes: quantities 
          of elements in the world, a players score, etc.</li>
        <li>Integers can automatically grow with time by setting the 'propagation 
          type' to fibonacci growth. This means that as the sim continues, from 
          round to round, the value will propagate in time by increasing.</li>
        <li>More formulas for growth (exponential, ramp increasing, etc.) will 
          be added in the future. Fibonacci was selected as one of the first since 
          it is extremely straightforward, and somewhat representative of early 
          growth in biological systems.</li>
      </ul>
